body: The rub is that out of date Flutter SDKs can produce unpredictable results (notably debugger issues). To that end, it would be great to show a toast and probably an error in the preference and project creation pages if this case is detected. Open question: what from our version info is right to key off? cc @abarth @sethladd since I think you guys were thinking about this?

comment_data.body: How do you want to define "too old" ?

> How do you want to define "too old" ?

I have no idea!

Maybe better to say it'd be great to test if a given SDK has feature "X", which we can derive somehow from it's date.  In SVN days, I'd just check for `>= $REV`.  Not sure what to do here.
There's a VERSION file in the root of the SDK.  We could bump that version every time the plugin wanted to make an assumption about a feature existing in the SDK.

Actually, that would be awesome.  Are there plans to bump this by anyone else that you're aware of?

@devoncarew : that should fit the bill eh?

> Are there plans to bump this by anyone else that you're aware of?

Not yet.  We'll still learning what it might be useful for.
My 0.02: I would put this on the back burner until there are more official releases (an alpha / stable channel).
@devoncarew for the first public release of the IJ plugin should we not at least check for a specific min version (which is the one we test against)?

> @devoncarew for the first public release of the IJ plugin should we not at least check for a specific min version (which is the one we test against)?

My gut too.  I think we can punt on the `VERSION` tweaks but it would be great to have some kind of check in place to ensure folks don't get snagged by stale flutter tools.
It sounds like the intent here is to capture super old installs of Flutter.
Can we have `flutter_tools` report how old it is?

We say "XX days ago" in --version:

```
~/Code/flutter/examples/flutter_gallery[master*] $ flutter --version
Flutter • channel master • git@github.com:flutter/flutter.git
Framework • revision 1b9c1bd2a9 (5 days ago) • 2016-10-06 15:32:03
Engine • revision f97caf271c
Tools • Dart 1.20.0-dev.10.1
```
@abarth, @sethladd  : after a bunch of discussion I think we converged on bumping the `VERSION` file after all.  Any objections to me doing that today?

title: Add a notification if the currently configured Flutter SDK is too old.
